==============================================
OPEN-SOURCE COMPONENTS USED
==============================================

EduMind is built using the following open-source libraries and tools:

1. Three.js (MIT License) - 3D rendering engine
   https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js

2. TalkingHead.js (MIT License) - 3D avatar with lip-sync
   https://github.com/met4citizen/TalkingHead

3. Firebase SDK (Apache 2.0 License) - Backend services
   https://firebase.google.com

4. Marked.js (MIT License) - Markdown parser
   https://github.com/markedjs/marked

5. DOMPurify (Apache 2.0 / Mozilla License) - XSS sanitizer
   https://github.com/cure53/DOMPurify

6. Ready Player Me - 3D avatar models
   https://readyplayer.me

All third-party open-source components remain under their respective licenses.
See individual component licenses for details.

==============================================
